// A parenthesized result list is either all named or all unnamed; a named result
// followed by a bare type, as below, leaves the trailing type with no name to
// bind and no type of its own to inherit, so it is rejected (like Go's "missing
// parameter type"). Note that "(int, a int)" is instead accepted: there the bare
// "int" is a result named int sharing the following result's type.

// ERROR "missing type for function result string"
func mixed() (a int, string)

func main() {
	println(1)
}
